Citation.sTitle: Solubility of d-Aspartic Acid and l-Aspartic Acid in Aqueous Salt Solutions from (293 to 343) K
Citation.sAbstract: The solubility of d-aspartic acid and l-aspartic acid in aqueous solutions of various molalities of sodium chloride and potassium chloride was measured by using a laser technique from (293 to 343) K at atmospheric pressure. Results showed that sodium chloride and potassium chloride have a salting-in effect on the solubility of d-aspartic acid and l-aspartic acid has the same phenomenon in sodium chloride solution. The solubility data were correlated by a semiempirical equation.
